Spanish police uncovered a major Barcelona sex trafficking ring on Monday. During the raid, authorities arrested eight men and one woman suspected of running the organization, and freed three young, impoverished Venezuelan women who had been lured to Spain while still living in Venezuela. The ongoing economic decline in Venezuela has led to an upswing in traffickers preying on desperation. These young Venezuelan women had agreed to work off a debt of three thousand euros after being promised that their travel arrangements and costs would be taken care of. The traffickers had promised them that upon arrival in Spain, they just have to work "a short amount of time" to pay back the money but would then be free of the obligation and free to start their new lives. The reality, however, was starkly different. Upon arriving in Barcelona, the life they faced was a living hell of exploitation, intimidation and coercion. The women were forced to cover their housing weekly trough their earnings and overworked, subject to comply with any of the demands of their overseers. Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
